
## Outline

The workshop covers important basics (e.g., pre-processing, tokenization, and part-of-speech tagging) as well as three types of analytic techniques: rule-based, supervised, and unsupervised methods (dictionary methods, topic models and machine learning, respectively).

13:00 to 16:00pm (Day 1) and the second part 9:30 to 16:00

Day 1: 3 hours

+ Overview
+ What is quantitative text analysis and why?

+ Pre-processsing
+ Tokenization
+ Part-of-speech tagging

+ rule-based methods (i.e. dictionaries)

Basic descriptives


Day 2: 6h 30 minutes

Unsupervised methods

Topic models
Structural topic models

Supervised methods

etc.



